An easy and tasty recipe using The Blend™ - Spicy Bolognese and Mushroom Pasta Shells #BlenditarianRecipe!  Mushrooms are a superfood and they work a treat in mince recipes. This recipe is 20% pork mince, 40% beef mince and 40% mushroom @australianmushroomgrowers 
 
Ingredients 
250g pork mince 
500g beef mince 
500g mushrooms (finely diced) 
2 brown onions (diced) 
1 jar passata 
Tomato Paste 
1 tin chopped tomatoes 
Chilli flakes (1 tbs or more if you like to up the spice) 
600ml cream 
Italian Herbs 
Salt and Pepper 
Garlic (6 cloves crushed – 4 for Bolognese and 2 for sauce) 
Parmesan 
Large Pasta Shells (conchiglioni) 
Basil 
Olive Oil 
 
Method 
- Turn on oven to 180C 
- Boil water, add salt and cook your pasta shells until before al dente (~8 mins). They’ll cook more in the oven. 
- In a large frying pan, add olive oil and cook garlic until fragrant. Add onion and sauté. Stir through chilli flakes. 
- Add in mince and mushrooms and cook through. 
- Stir through tomato paste, tomatoes, salt and pepper, Italian herbs and basil and simmer for a few minutes. Put into a bowl and cool. 
- In a jug add garlic, half a cup of parmesan, cream, passata, salt and pepper and more chilli flakes if you like the spice. Stir until combined. 
In a large baking tray start to fill pasta shells with Bolognese and line them up in the tray. 
- Pour over sauce and then grate on more parmesan. Put in oven for 25 minutes. 
- Dinner time! (add on some fresh basil for some nice green) 
(This amount makes two trays or with leftover bolognese to freeze for next time)

Quick and easy dinners are a favourite! And this chicken and risoni ticks the box for tasty and ready fairly quickly.
In a bowl combine:
* 1 tbsp dried thyme
* 1 tbsp dried oregano
* 1 tbsp chilli flakes
* 1 tsp garlic powder
* 1 tbsp black pepper
* 1 tsp salt
* Juice from 1 lemon
* 3 tbsp olive oil
Coat two skin on chicken breasts and sit for 10 minutes. I used chicken breast, but am sure thigh would work nicely too and would probably be quicker, but I haven’t been able to find somewhere that sells skin on thigh? 
In a big hot pan fry your chicken breast on each side for around five mins so it gets some nice colour. I then took it out and popped in the air fryer for 15 mins on 200C to ensure they were cooked through. 
Then in that same pan, turn down the heat and pop a little olive oil, along with half a diced Spanish onion and five cloves of garlic minced, then cook til fragrant. Next add your punnet of cherry tomatoes, cook for a few mins, then add 1 cup of @barillaaus risoni and stir through. Add in 2 cups of chicken stock, reduce the heat and cook per risoni directions, which was 12 mins for this @barilla risoni. When nearly ready through a bag of English spinach and serve with your sliced chook on top. Yum! #perthmunchkin #homecooking #recipe #chicken #campbells #barilla #barillapasta #easyrecipes

Chicken Fricassee ❤️ This is one of my favourite dishes my dad would cook us growing up. A delish combo of chicken, asparagus, carrot and celery. Made with cans of @campbells cream of asparagus soup and plenty of chopped up chook and veg, it’s easy peasy and served with rice. It is my go to comfort food and like a big hug ❤️ Plus if you make this giant amount of it, it freezes really well for when you feel like having it again. Thanks for the recipe dad!
Ingredients
- 6 x Chicken Breast
- 3 tins x Campbells cream of asparagus soup
- 1 jar asparagus spears
- 3-4 bunches of fresh asparagus
- 6-8 celery sticks
- 6 carrots
- 1 tsp Maggi seasoning 
- 1 bunch parsley 🌿.

Prepare these skewers ahead of time to take to your next BBQ! 🍡

With only a few simple, seasonal ingredients, this recipe brings together flavours perfectly: 

1. Combine chopped herbs and olive oil in a small bowl. Cut feta into 2cm cubes and toss in oil mix.

2. Using a vegetable peeler, create baby zucchini strips by shaving lengthwise.

3. Place a cherry tomato into a skewer and then take a zucchini strip, wrapping it around a feta cube securely in one direction. Allow the zucchini a generous overlap before trimming off excess and add immediately to skewer to hold in place.

4. Repeat until each skewer is full. Brush outside of each skewer with remaining olive oil mix from the feta marinade.

5. Heat a griddle pan until hot. Cook skewers for 3-4 minutes on each side, or until the zucchini is browned.
